<paragraph blockId="2.[177,1085,264,486]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">
C o m m e n t: The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="KRAATZ 1862" authorityName="KRAATZ" authorityYear="1862" box="[478,769,347,369]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Borboropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[478,611,347,369]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">Borboropora</emphasis>
KRAATZ 1862
</taxonomicName>
currently includes only three species, all of them distributed in the Western Palaearctic region and all of them rare to extremely rare (ASSING in press; 
<bibRefCitation author="SMETANA A" box="[515,678,405,427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473" pagination="353 - 494" refId="ref4198" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Staphylinidae, subfamily Aleocharinae, pp. 353 - 494. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. II. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. Stenstrup, Apollo Books: 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA 2004</bibRefCitation>
): the widespread 
<typeStatus box="[855,899,406,427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">type</typeStatus>
species 
<emphasis box="[986,1085,405,427]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">B. kraatzi</emphasis>
FUSS 1862, the recently described 
<taxonomicName authority="ASSING" authorityName="ASSING" box="[530,787,435,457]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Borboropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrmecophila">
<emphasis box="[530,704,435,457]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">B. myrmecophila</emphasis>
ASSING
</taxonomicName>
in press (southern 
<collectingCountry box="[982,1073,435,457]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="WEISE" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[220,318,465,486]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Borboropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reitteri">
<emphasis box="[220,318,465,486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">B. reitteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[177,1085,501,787]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">
The original description of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="WEISE" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[462,562,502,523]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Borboropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reitteri">
<emphasis box="[462,562,502,523]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">B. reitteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a single 
<typeStatus box="[781,870,501,523]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen from &quot;den transsylvanischen Alpen bei Oberkerz&quot; deposited in the Weise collection (
<bibRefCitation author="WEISE J" box="[943,1073,530,552]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473" pagination="3 - 30" refId="ref4251" refString="WEISE J. (1877): Pseudoscopaeus Reitteri; pp. 9 - 10. - In: REITTER E.: Coleopterologische Ergebnisse einer Reise nach Sudungarn und in die Transsylvanischen Alpen. - Verhandlungen des Naturforschenden Vereins in Brunn 15 (1876): 3 - 30." type="journal article" year="1877">WEISE 1877</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<taxonomicName box="[224,363,560,582]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Staphylinidae</taxonomicName>
from the Weise collection are deposited in the &quot;Dt. Ent. Inst. 
<collectingRegion box="[1004,1071,560,582]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">Berlin</collectingRegion>
&quot;, today the Deutsches Entomologisches Institut in Müncheberg (
<bibRefCitation author="HORN W &amp; KAHLE I &amp; FRIESE G" box="[824,1008,589,611]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473" refId="ref4044" refString="HORN W., KAHLE I., FRIESE G. &amp; R. GAEDIKE (1990): Collectiones entomologicae. Ein Kompendium uber den Verbleib entomologischer Sammlungen der Welt bis 1960. - Akademie der Landwirtschaftswissenschaften der Deutschen Demokratischen Republik, Berlin: 573 pp." type="book" year="1990">HORN et al. 1990</bibRefCitation>
). However, according to the curator in charge, the 
<typeStatus box="[656,745,618,640]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">holotype</typeStatus>
cannot be found (ZERCHE pers. comm.) and a subsequent search in the collections of the HNHM, where the Reitter collection is deposited, did not yield any results either (MAKRANCZY pers. comm.), suggesting that the 
<typeStatus box="[351,440,706,728]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">holotype</typeStatus>
is probably lost. The forebody and the previously unknown female sexual characters are illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[609,695,735,757]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="1.[177,217,1481,1503]" captionTargetBox="[177,1081,768,1433]" captionTargetId="figure-133@1.[177,1090,969,1446]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-5: Borboropora reitteri (WEISE) (Sardinia): (1) forebody; (2) antenna; (3) posterior portion of female tergite VIII; (4) female sternite VIII; (5) spermatheca. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-4: 0.2 mm; 5: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276209/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">Figs 1-5</figureCitation>
; males have not become available for study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[177,1085,802,912]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">
Records of this species are extremely rare. After the original description, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="WEISE" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[941,1041,803,824]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Borboropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reitteri">
<emphasis box="[941,1041,803,824]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">B. reitteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had only once been reported again from the 
<collectingCountry box="[617,783,831,853]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="HORION A" box="[802,951,831,853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="473" refId="ref4007" refString="HORION A. (1967): Faunistik der mitteleuropaischen Kafer. Bd. XI: Staphylinidae, 3. Teil: Habrocerinae bis Aleocharinae (ohne Subtribus Athetae). - Uberlingen-Bodensee: 419 pp." type="book" year="1967">HORION 1967</bibRefCitation>
). The above specimens from Sardinia and 
<collectingCountry box="[504,574,860,882]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">Bosnia</collectingCountry>
represent first records from 
<collectingCountry box="[897,943,860,882]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">Italy</collectingCountry>
and Bosnia- 
<collectingCountry box="[177,310,890,912]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">Herzegovina</collectingCountry>
. The currently known distribution is illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[818,885,890,912]" captionStart="Map 1" captionStartId="2.[177,222,1551,1572]" captionTargetBox="[177,1091,928,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-315@2.[177,1091,928,1527]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Map 1: Distribution of Borboropora reitteri (WEISE); the record from Bosnia-Herzegovina without specified locality is placed near Sarajevo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276211" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276211/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="473">Map 1</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
